'''Electronics Corporation of India Limited (ECIL)''' ('''भारत इलेक्ट्रॉनिक्स निगम लिमिटेड ( ईसीआईएल ) ''') is a [[Government of India]] Enterprise under the [[Department of Atomic Energy (India)|Department of Atomic Energy]], established on April 11, 1967 by [[A. S. Rao]] at [[Hyderabad, India|Hyderabad]], to create a strong indigenous base in [[electronics]]. ECIL is a multi-product, multi disciplinary organisation with focus on indigenous [[Nuclear power|Nuclear energy]], [[Outer space|space]] and [[Defence industry|Defence]] sectors. ECIL also has a strong presence in indigenous [[Cyber Security|Electronic Security]], [[Telecommunication|Communications]], [[Computer Network|Networking]] and [[e-governance]] domains. ECIL has committed partnerships with nuclear energy establishments of [[India]], particularly [[Bhabha Atomic Research Center]] (BARC), [[Nuclear Power Corporation of India Limited]] (NPCIL) and [[Indira Gandhi Centre for Atomic Research]] (IGCAR). ECIL also actively supports other strategic sectors such as indigenous Defence ([[Defence Research and Development Organisation]] (DRDO)), Space ([[Department of Space]] (India))Civil Aviation, Information and Broadcasting, Telecommunications, Insurance, Banking, Police and Para-military Forces, Oil and Gas, Power, Space Education, Health, Agriculture, Steel and Coal.

ECIL is credited with producing the first indigenous [[digital computer]]s, TDC 312 and TDC 316, [[solid state (electronics)|solid state]] TV, control and instrumentation for [[nuclear power plants]] and first earth station antenna of India.{{citation needed|date=July 2017}}

ECIL won Environment Protection Award for the year 2012 in the category "R&D and Other Units Group".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ecil.co.in/news/AERB_Award_on_Environment_Protection_to_ECIL.pdf?dv=1 |title=Fax message, 23 September 2013 |website=Ecil.co.in |accessdate=15 July 2017}}</ref>

== Products ==
Present product range of ECIL includes:

*[[Nuclear power|Nuclear]] sector: Control and instrumentation products for [[nuclear power plants]];  Integrated [[security systems]] for [[Nuclear power|nuclear]] installations;  [[Radiation monitoring]] instruments; Secured network of all [[Department of Atomic Energy (India)]] units via [[satellite]].
*[[Defence industry|Defence]] Sector:  Various types of [[Fuse (explosives)|fuse]]s;  [[V/UHF]] Radio communication equipment;  [[Electronics warfare system]]s and derivatives; [[Thermal batteries]] and special components for [[missile]] projects;  Precision [[Servomechanism|servo]] components like [[gyros]];  [[Missile]] support control and command systems; [[Training simulators]]; Stabilised [[Antenna (radio)|antenna]] and tracking for [[Light Combat Aircraft]];  Detection and pre-detonation of explosive devices;  [[Radar jamming and deception|Jammers]] with direction finding abilities.
*Commercial Sector:  [[Indian voting machines|Electronic voting machines]];<ref>{{cite web|title=ECIL expects 10-lakh VVPAT units order from EC|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/ecil-expects-10-lakh-vvpat-units-order-from-ec/1/629755.html|website=indiatoday.intoday.in|accessdate=15 July 2017|date=March 29, 2016}}</ref><ref>http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/ecil-expects-10-lakh-vvpat-units-order-from-ec/1/629755.html</ref> [[Voter-verified paper audit trail]];<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/pti-stories/ecil-expects-10-lakh-vvpat-units-order-from-ec-116032900630_1.html|title=ECIL expects 10-lakh VVPAT units order from EC}}</ref><ref>http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/hyderabad/ECIL-expects-10-lakh-VVPAT-units-order-from-EC/articleshow/51599255.cms</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://eci.nic.in/eci_main1/Current/ImpIns_24092015.pdf|title=General Election to the State Legislative Assembly of Bihar, 2015- Use of EVMs with Voter Verifiable Paper Audit Trail System(VVPAT)-reg.}}</ref> [[Totaliser]];<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/New+counting+method+for+Assembly+polls/1/21718.html|title=New counting method for Assembly polls}}</ref> [[Wireless local loop]] (WLL) systems; antenna products; electronic energy meters or [[electricity meter]]; [[X-ray]] baggage inspection system for airports; computer hardware, software and services; computer education services.

